## 🤖 AI-Assisted Microscope Selection

Choosing the right microscope for your specific biological question can be challenging. Because our facility maintains a highly structured, machine-readable database of all our hardware, you can use AI assistants (like ChatGPT, Claude, or Copilot) to recommend the best system for your needs based on our *actual* inventory!

### Step 1: Download our Facility Database
Download the latest snapshot of our microscope inventory. This file contains all the technical specifications, modalities, and available lasers/objectives for every system.

[⬇️ Download `instruments_data.json`](assets/instruments_data.json){: .md-button .md-button--primary style="margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;" }

### Step 2: Open your preferred AI Assistant
Go to your preferred AI tool (e.g., ChatGPT, Claude) and ensure it supports file uploads.

### Step 3: Upload the file and use this prompt
Upload the `instruments_data.json` file you just downloaded. Then, copy and paste the prompt below, filling in the bracketed `[ ]` information with your specific experimental details:

<div class="admonition abstract">
  <p class="admonition-title">Copy and paste this into the AI:</p>
  <p>I have attached a JSON file containing the exact inventory of microscopes in my core facility. I need to plan an imaging experiment. Here are my requirements:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sample type:</strong> [e.g., Live cells, fixed tissue slice, organoids, cleared brain]</li>
    <li><strong>Fluorophores / Dyes:</strong> [e.g., DAPI, Alexa Fluor 488, mCherry]</li>
    <li><strong>Key requirements:</strong> [e.g., Fast volumetric imaging, super-resolution, deep tissue penetration, multi-well plate screening, long-term incubation]</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Based ONLY on the microscopes available in the attached file, which 1 or 2 systems would you recommend and why? Please mention the specific modality, objective, and light source that make it a good fit.</p>
</div>

